cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.DB, cs.CL, cs.DL 

This paper presents a novel consequence-based calculus for reasoning in description logics, specifically for the SRIQ DL. Therefore, it is likely to be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Additionally, the paper deals with reasoning algorithms and DLs, which are related to databases and natural language processing, respectively. Hence, it could also be categorized under cs.DB (Databases) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, since the paper proposes an extension to existing reasoning algorithms, it could be categorized under cs.DL (Digital Libraries).
